This README file is written by Trent Balius, 2023/05/24


Here, a template pipeline for HDB (and more) ligand generation is described ("$DOCK6BASE/template_pipeline/hdb_lig_gen").

This is a set of scripts that are associated with this paper:

Balius, Tan, Chakrabarti, DOCK 6: Incorporating hierarchical traversal through precomputed ligand conformations to enable large-scale docking


These scripts where taken from a modified version of DOCK 3.7/3.8.

there are four directories
 common
 mol2db2
 amsol
 generate


# The directory “common” contains a set of python modules/libraries that are used by other programs. 


# The directory “mol2db2” contains the mol2db2 program that writes out a db2 file for docking.   

     For information about this program see the help print out provided below.   
     python mol2db2/mol2db2.py --help
     Usage: mol2db2.py [options]
     
     Convert multimol2 and solv files into db2 files
     
     Options:
       -h, --help            show this help message and exit
       -v, --verbose         lots of debugging output
       --covalent            make a DOCKovalent compatible db (assumes SiH2 dummy
                             atom)
       -a, --time            timing output
       -m MOL2FILE, --mol2=MOL2FILE
                             multimol2 input file, (default: db.mol2.gz)
       -n NAMEFILE, --namemol2=NAMEFILE
                             mol2 name file, (default: name.txt)
       -s SOLVFILE, --solv=SOLVFILE
                             solv input file, (default: db.solv)
       -o DB2GZFILE, --db=DB2GZFILE
                             db2.gz output file, (default: db.db2.gz)
       -t ATOMTYPEFILE, --atomtype=ATOMTYPEFILE
                             atom type conversion file, (default: none)
       -c COLORTABLEFILE, --colortable=COLORTABLEFILE
                             color table conversion file, (default: none)
       -d CLASHFILE, --clash=CLASHFILE
                             clash checking parameter file, (default: none)
       -y HYDROGENFILE, --hydrogens=HYDROGENFILE
                             terminal hydrogen parameter file, (default: none)
       -r, --noreseth        reset the planar terminal hydrogen positions,
                             (default: True)
       -z, --norotateh       rotate the terminal hydrogen positions, (default:
                             True)
       -x TOLERANCE, --disttol=TOLERANCE
                             distance tolerance in angstroms, (default: 0.001)
       -l LIMITSET, --limitset=LIMITSET
                             limit on the number of sets, (default: 2500000)
       --limitconf=LIMITCONF
                             limit on the number of confs, (default: 200000)
       --limitcoord=LIMITCOORD
                             limit on the number of coords, (default: 1000000)
       --maxrecursiondepth=MAXRECURSIONDEPTH
                             Max recursive subdivision steps to take (default: 1)
     
# The directory amsol contains the scripts used to run and process amsol7.1.  The amsol program is used for calculating the partial charges and per-atom desolvation parameters used for db2 generation.  These scripts have a dependance on amsol being installed. 
Amsol is available here: 

https://comp.chem.umn.edu/amsol/
https://comp.chem.umn.edu/sds/amsol/amsol.cgi

Here are the scripts in the amsol directory: 

* amsol/process_amsol_mol2.py

   This script processes the amsol output.
   
   python amsol/process_amsol_mol2.py
    This script needs the following:
    (1) amsol water output file
    (2) amsol hex output file
    (3) amsol hex output file
    (4) outputprefix
   

* amsol/make_amsol71_input.py

   This script will make the input files needed to run amsol.
   This script takes two parameters as input:
      path_and_file_ZmatMOPAC
      Molecule Name
  
   make_amsol71_input.py needs a ZmatMOPAC file as input.
   The ZmatMOPAC file must have been generated by 'obabel ... -o mopin ...' (MOPAC Internals)
   Make sure that obabel is installed on your computer !!!

   This script will read in a smiles file based on the path of the ZmatMOPAC file and will use RdKit to calculate the formal charge for that smiles.   


* amsol/make_amsol71_input_use_mol2_charges.py

  This script is very similar to amsol/make_amsol71_input.py
  Based on the path of the ZmatMOPAC this script will read in a mol2 file and calculate the formal charge based on the partial charges in that mol2 file.  


* amsol/mol2amsol.py

  This is a mol2 library with functions for reading and writing mol2 files.

* amsol/calc_solvation.csh

  This script will run amsol using the above python scripts.  It uses the “amsol/make_amsol71_input.py” script.   

* amsol/calc_solvation_formal_charge_from_mol2.csh

  This script will run amsol using the above python scripts.  It uses the “amsol/make_amsol71_input.py” script.   


In this directory there is also a patch that can be applied to amsol before compiling: 

* amsol/patches/amsol7.1_port_intcar.f.diff

  See the following wiki page: 
  https://wiki.docking.org/index.php?title=AMSOL#Patches

 
* amsol/amsol7.1

  We expect that the executable or a link to the executable be present in this directory:



# The directory “generate” contains a bunch of shell scripts that are used for preparing small molecules for docking.  These scripts will generate dock ready file formats including db2.gz files and mol2 files.  These scripts work on our system and are provided as a courtesy.  Users will need to modify these scripts, before they will work on their system.  

These scripts have a number of dependencies including: python3 with RdKit and numpy, chemaxon, corina, and amsol.   

Here are the scripts with a brief description:
 
* mol2tosmi_rdkit.py

  This python script converts a mol2 file to a smiles file.
  Dependencies: Python3 with RdKit.  

* build_ligand_simple_2Dto3D.csh

  This script will convert a smiles file to mol2 files.  
  It will protonate and tautomerize the smiles and make a mol2 for each
  Dependencies: python3 with RdKit, chemaxon, corina, and amsol.   

* build_ligand_simple_dock6_covalent.csh

  This script will convert a smiles file to mol2 files for running attach-and-grow covalent docking in DOCK6.  
  It will protonate and tautomerize the smiles and make a mol2 for each
  Dependencies: python3 with RdKit, chemaxon, corina, and amsol.   

* build_ligand_simple_2Dto3D_smi_as_is.csh

  This script will make a mol2 file based on the smiles as-is (it assumes that the charge state and tautomer is as you want it).  
  Dependencies: python3 with RdKit, chemaxon, corina, and amsol.

* build_ligand_mol2_with_dock6.sh

  This script will make a db2.gz file based on the mol2 file as-is but molecule does not need to have partial charges.  
  Dependencies: python3 with RdKit, amsol.

    * build_ligand_mol2_with_dock6_more_sampling.sh


* build_ligand_charged_mol2_with_dock6.sh

  This script will make a db2.gz file based on the mol2 file as is using the formal charge of the mol2 file.  
  Dependencies: python3, amsol.

* build_ligand_simple_with_dock6.csh

  This script will convert a smiles file to db2.gz files.  
  It will protonate and tautomerize the smiles and make a db2.gz files for each.
  Dependencies: python3 with RdKit, chemaxon, corina, and amsol.   
  (dock6 is used as the conformation generation tool). 

  The following scripts are variances of build_ligand_simple_with_dock6.csh:
    * build_ligand_simple_with_dock6_high_ph.csh
    * build_ligand_simple_with_dock6_low_ph.csh
    * build_ligand_simple_with_dock6_more_rings.csh
    * build_ligand_simple_with_dock6_increased_sampling.csh

